oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Plumhead Parakeet Indoor Breeding Tips
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Rasoletti, Lynn
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Since I saw my first plumheadparakeet in a local pet shop, I've wantedto breed the bird. The beautiful stainedglass colors on these haughty, aloofbirds combined with their electronicflute-like calls had me mesmerized.Their flight is a soft, whirring whoosh.They remind me of miniature pheasantsflying with those long tail feathers.But, I've found them quite a challengeto breed indoors, especially ifspace is limited. After much experimentingand many failures, here's whatworks for me.
